    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="1096"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1096">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/4105.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Davis</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Diego, California</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 5, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>British Vice Consul, Guadalajara, Percy G. Holmes, to whom I turned over American
                    Consulate there and the care all American interests that district telegraphs
                    British Consul, San Diego, that confiscation properties threatened all cases
                    where rents, taxes or wages employees refugee Americans are unpaid. I assured
                    Mr. Holmes would be reimbursed assistance furnished Americans and he especially
                    promised furnish transportation cases needed to Manzanillo. I had already
                    furnished transportation some who did not get away with us.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Will B. Davis</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
